   "author_association" : "MEMBER",
   "body" : "Currently the HTTP server initialization (`HTTPBindAddresses`) fails only when *all* bindings fail. So if multiple binds are specified (`127.0.0.1` and `::1` by defeault) and one succeeds and the other fails, the latter is essentially ignored.\r\n\r\nThis commit changes the error behavior to fail *if not all* binds could be performed, which I think is more in line with how software normally handles this and what users expect.\r\n\r\nNeeds mention in release notes.",
